<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Ember & Grain — Our Story</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <main class="main-content">
    <section class="hero-section">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Est. 2019</p>
      <h2 class="hero-title">A slow burn,<br/><em>built to last</em></h2>
      <p class="hero-sub">23 Kettle Lane, Maplewood</p>
    </section>

    <div class="story-body">

      <div class="story-block story-block--lead">
        <p class="story-lead">
          Ember &amp; Grain started as a single table, a hand-me-down Chemex, and a stubborn belief
          that a truly great cup of coffee could anchor a neighbourhood.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-block story-block--split">
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-heading">Where it began</h3>
          <p>
            Founders Maya and Soren met at a roastery in Antwerp in 2016. They spent three years
            travelling — Ethiopia, Colombia, Sumatra — learning how altitude, fermentation, and
            processing unlock wildly different flavour from the same plant.
          </p>
          <p>
            Back home in Maplewood, they converted a narrow hardware shop on Kettle Lane into a
            19-seat café. The original penny-tile floor is still there. So is the hand-lettered
            chalkboard Maya drew on opening day.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="story-stat-stack">
          <div class="story-stat">
            <span class="story-stat-num">6</span>
            <span class="story-stat-label">origin countries sourced</span>
          </div>
          <div class="story-stat">
            <span class="story-stat-num">19</span>
            <span class="story-stat-label">seats, always intentional</span>
          </div>
          <div class="story-stat">
            <span class="story-stat-num">4–6</span>
            <span class="story-stat-label">week bean rotation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="story-divider">
        <span>✦</span>
      </div>

      <div class="story-block story-block--values">
        <h3 class="story-heading">What we believe</h3>
        <div class="values-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-icon">◎</span>
            <h4>Traceability first</h4>
            <p>Every bean on our menu comes with a farm name, a farmer's name, and a harvest date. No exceptions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-icon">◈</span>
            <h4>Slow by design</h4>
            <p>We don't rush extraction. We don't rush service. The best things — coffee, community — take time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-icon">◇</span>
            <h4>Fair at every link</h4>
            <p>We pay above-market rates directly to producers and publish our pricing chain annually.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="story-divider">
        <span>✦</span>
      </div>

      <div class="story-block story-block--cta">
        <p class="story-cta-text">Come in. Pull up a stool. We'll make you something worth sitting down for.</p>
        <div class="story-cta-actions">
          <a href="/hours" class="btn btn--primary">See our hours</a>
          <a href="/order" class="btn btn--ghost">Order ahead</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <footer class="page-footer">
      <p>Follow the journey <strong>@emberandgrain</strong> · hello@emberandgrain.com</p>
      <p class="footer-small">Ember & Grain · 23 Kettle Lane, Maplewood · Est. 2019</p>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <script src="/js/nav.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
